MyBroadband has seen a big increase in the number of companies advertising with it, and the number of campaigns they are running. As the largest ICT news website in South Africa and a top choice for ICT decision makers, MyBroadband is the perfect partner for ICT companies. ICT executives and managers; CEOs, CTOs, and CIOs; directors; business owners; and IT decision makers visit MyBroadband every day for the latest news and to learn about new developments in the industry. As a result, companies which advertise on MyBroadband get excellent exposure to these ICT decision makers. MyBroadband has seen a strong increase in the number of companies advertising on its platforms. Since its establishment, there has been consistent growth in the number of clients on MyBroadband – including through tough economic conditions in South Africa from 2017 to 2019. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-329987" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MyBroadband.jpg" alt="MyBroadband" width="640" height="545" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MyBroadband.jpg 771w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MyBroadband-469x400.jpg 469w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MyBroadband-505x430.jpg 505w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MyBroadband-768x654.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The reason companies want to advertise on MyBroadband is simple: it is the only place to reach South Africa’s entire ICT industry at once. With over 1.4 million ICT decision makers reading MyBroadband every month, companies are able to reach top-level executives and business owners along with IT managers and techies in one place. The return on investment companies receive from their advertising campaigns on MyBroadband then make establishing a long-term commercial partnership an easy decision. As a result, MyBroadband continues to see increases in the number of companies partnering with it, and the number of campaigns they run. To find out more, contact Kevin Lancaster on kevin@mybroadband.co.za This article was published in partnership with MyBroadband.